                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=norm2782",
                        "name": "norm2782",
                        "displayName": "Jurrien Stutterheim",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Could you give me a simple use-case including:\n\n- A simple UNION query\n- A COUNT query, based on that UNION query.\n\nThis will help me greatly in formulating a patch.\n\n\nCheers,\n\n\n- Jurri\u00ebn",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=norm2782",
                        "name": "norm2782",
                        "displayName": "Jurrien Stutterheim",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-26T14:33:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-26T14:33:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31370",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=saphir2k",
                        "name": "saphir2k",
                        "displayName": "Thorsten Ruf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Here are the two use-cases:\n\n{code:title=simple UNION query}\n$select1->from('user',array('firstname','lastname'));\n$select1->where('id = ?',1);\n        \n$select2 = $this->db->select();\n$select2->from('user',array('firstname','lastname'));\n$select2->where('id = ?',2);\n        \n$selectUnion = $this->db->select();    \n$selectUnion->union(array($select1,$select2));\n{code}\n\nIts hard to create a fast count with a union statement, i'm pretty sure this one is the slowest. Hopefully a database expert is watching this issue. ;-)\n\n{code:title=count with union statement}\n$select1->from('user',array('firstname','lastname'));\n$select1->where('id = ?',1);\n        \n$select2 = $this->db->select();\n$select2->from('user',array('firstname','lastname'));\n$select2->where('id = ?',2);\n        \n$selectUnion = $this->db->select();    \n$selectUnion->union(array($select1,$select2));\n\n\/\/ Wrap a SELECT count(*) statement around the union \n$selectCount = $this->db->select();     \n$selectCount->from($selectUnion,'count(*)');\n\n{code}\n\nRegards,\nThorsten\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=saphir2k",
                        "name": "saphir2k",
                        "displayName": "Thorsten Ruf",
                        "active": true
                    },
